<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-249-398  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 249 398.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  April 1990 v3 n4 p48(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Is Applause II a contender? (Software Review) (Ashton-TateApplause II presentation graphics package)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ellison, Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ashton-Tate (products).andO;Product:   Applause II (Presentation software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Presentation SoftwareEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Is Applause II a Contender? If Applause II had entered the ring when it wasscheduled to, last fall, it could have been a contender for graphics users'hearts.andM;But long delays sent users into the Freelance Plus corner, and rumors of aHarvard Graphics upgrade may keep those impatient fans from switching camps.andO;Newcomers to PC graphics, however, ought to give this excellent upgrade tothe MasterGraphics and Draw Applause programs serious consideration; it hasas much power as any other business graphics package, and it's more fun.andM;In fact, few PC graphics products rival Applause II's ability and finesse.andO;It's graphical.andP;  It's interactive.andP;  It makes excellent use of the mouse.andO;Best of all, it abandons the stodgy fill-in-the-form approach to creatingcharts that is used by Freelance, Harvard, and 35mm Express.andP;  Instead,Applause uses an onscreen spreadsheet.andP;  When you don't see the spreadsheet,you see your chart.andM;Applause supports 37 kinds of data charts, builds org charts with uncannyskill, provides 18 templates for word charts, and lets you create templates.andO;It provides a rainbow of lavish colors and features a dazzling library ofbackgrounds and clip art.andM;The screenshow facility offers a Present screen where you can preview yourpresentation images, edit their order, and specify transitional effects.andP;  Ifyou use slides, you can send chart files by modem directly to the Ashton-TateGraphics Service for processing and next-day delivery.andO;</TEXT></DOC>